
Object class in java
--------------------
Object class is the parent class of every class in java. Every class whether directly or indirectly extends Object class. 

For ex : 
   i.  class Hello extends Object {

    }
    here Hello class directly extends Object class

   ii. class Parent extends Object{
        .....
       }
       class child extends Parent{
        ......
       }
        Here Parent class directly extends Parent class whereas Child class indirectly extends Object class .

    There are some methods of Object class : 
        1. toString()
        2. hashCode()
        3. equals()
        4. getClass()
        5. finalize()
        6. clone()
        7. wait()
            |-- wait(arg)
            |-- wait(arg1, arg2)
        8. notify()
        9. notifyAll()